            <section id="media-2">
                <h2><span>Latest Article</span></h2>
                <div id="media-latest">
                    <div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-47/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-47/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>Relationships among Incoloy 800, 800H and 800HT</span></h4><p class="media-p">Incoloy 800, Incoloy 800H and Incoloy 800HT are very similar. They differ only slightly in their carbon, aluminium and titanium content. In this article, we will explain the relationship and differences between these three alloys.</p><time class="media-time">2022.04.12</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-46/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-46/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>Annealing or Bright Annealing? Why is ...</span></h4><p class="media-p">Why do materials need to be annealed? Why keep the material bright when annealed? When is bright annealing required? In this article, we will explain the whole thing from scratch.</p><time class="media-time">2022.04.05</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-44/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-44/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>Inconel Alloy 600 VS Inconel Alloy 601</span></h4><p class="media-p">Inconel 601 added more chromium on the basis of Inconel 600. So their main difference is the difference in antioxidant properties. In this article, we will compare the similarities and differences between the two alloys in several aspects.</p><time class="media-time">2022.03.29</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-42/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-42/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>Introducing 3 Creep Processes of Superalloys</span></h4><p class="media-p">In this article, we will study the whole creep process in detail, and the influence of different factors on the creep process. This allows us to better control the life cycle of the parts in the actual project.</p><time class="media-time">2022.03.22</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-41/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-41/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>5 Methods to Test / Inspect Nickel Alloys</span></h4><p class="media-p">When importing nickel alloy products, we believe you will have a lot of worries. In this article, we introduce 5 methods for controlling the quality of alloys. This can help you avoid 99% of material quality risks.</p><time class="media-time">2022.03.14</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-40/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-40/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>Inconel 601 Filler Metal Sent to Australia</span></h4><p class="media-p">On March 10, 2022, we shipped a batch of Inconel 601 Filler Metal (AWS A5.14 ERNiCrFe-11) to our Australian customer. We pride ourselves on our speed of delivery and logistics.</p><time class="media-time">2022.03.10</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-39/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-39/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>8 Trustworthy Suppliers for Nickel Alloy</span></h4><p class="media-p">In this article, we will recommend 8 trustworthy nickel alloy suppliers. It allows you to make better decisions in the purchasing process.</p><time class="media-time">2022.03.07</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-43/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-43/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>Incoloy A-286 Rod Sent to South Korea</span></h4><p class="media-p">On January 6, 2022, we supplied a batch of high quality Incoloy A-286 rod to our Korean customer. They have high dimensional requirements and mechanical performance requirements for materials.</p><time class="media-time">2022.02.09</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-45/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-45/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>Inconel 625 Wire Sent to United Kingdom</span></h4><p class="media-p">On December 14, 2021, We sent a batch of Inconel 625 wire to the UK. During the entire order period, we went through the epidemic and experienced power outages. In the end, with our efforts, the entire order was delivered smoothly.</p><time class="media-time">2021.12.20</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div><div class="point"></div><div class="media-blog"><a href="/AEETHER/media/media-38/media.html"><img src="/AEETHER/media/media-38/mediapic1.jpg" alt="title image for articles"><h4><span>The Role of Aluminum in Superalloys</span></h4><p class="media-p">Aluminum plays a very important role in some superalloys. This article will fully let you understand why aluminum is added to some alloys.</p><time class="media-time">2021.12.13</time><div class="media-div">Learn More</div></a></div>                </div>
            </section>
